body:
Hi!

I'm trying to use @Siemienik [xlsx-renderer](https://github.com/Siemienik/xlsx-renderer) library with React, like this:
```javascript
import { Renderer } from "xlsx-renderer";
// ...
 async function testingXlsxRenderer() {
    const renderer = new Renderer();
    const viewModel = {
      title: "testing",
      items: [/*.. my array ..*/],
    };
    const result = await renderer.renderFromFile(
      "./hts-template.xlsx",
      viewModel
    );
    await result.xlsx.writeFile("./my-awesome-report.xlsx");
  }
```

But I'm getting the following error:
```
Uncaught (in promise) TypeError: Cannot read property 'F_OK' of undefined
    at exceljs.min.js:3
    at new Promise (<anonymous>)
    at Object.exists (exceljs.min.js:3)
    at e.<anonymous> (exceljs.min.js:3)
...
```

When using:
"react": "^16.13.1",
"xlsx-renderer": "^2.2.3"

xlsx-renderer's exceljs version: "3.8.1"

**EDIT:** related to https://github.com/Siemienik/xlsx-renderer/issues/13#issuecomment-704589977
